What you need to know:

“It is a good win for us because we continue to keep teams at the top of the league on toes. My players followed my instructions and that is what aided us to score and contain our opponents,” Ayany told Nation Sport.At Bukhungu stadium in Kakamega, MCF shocked host Soy United at home as Kelvin Ochieng’s 52nd minute strike decided the tough tie between the two teams.